madrid , spain -lrb- ap -rrb- _ the spanish hotel giant sol melia announced monday it will merge its various units to create a hotel group it said will be the world 's ninth largest . sol melia , owned by the escarrer family , will fully absorb melia inversiones americanas , which specializes in latin america and the caribbean , and the family 's private hotel-construction business inmotel . sol melia , spain 's largest hotel management company , operates more than 250 hotels and handles some 65,000 rooms in 25 countries . founded by gabriel escarrer in 1956 with the first sol hotel , it became the center of his family 's hotel empire . `` the integration of the three companies into one will provide greater financial stability that will allow us to maximize opportunities for future growth and have a leading position in the world , '' escarrer , the company 's chairman , said in a press release monday . the merger operation will be concluded in the first quarter of 1999 and will reduce company costs . 